Class GraphicElement

  • java.lang.Object
    • handlers.GraphicElement

  • public class GraphicElement
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains the data values required to place a graphic element on the screen from specified x and y start and end positions, with a specified time, solid property, and specified shape and shading color.
    Version:
    1.2 (05.03.15)
    Author:
    Copyright (c) 2015 EyeHouse Ltd. All rights reserved.

    • Constructor Detail

      • GraphicElement

        public GraphicElement(java.lang.String type,
              float xstart,
              float ystart,
              float xend,
              float yend,
              float duration,
              boolean solid,
              java.lang.String graphiccolor,
              java.lang.String shadingcolor)
        Constructor method for GraphicElement object.
        Parameters:
        type - The shape to be drawn on the canvas ( rectangle/oval/line )
        xstart - Horizontal position of the top-left of the graphic, relative to the resolution of the screen
        ystart - Vertical position of the top-left of the graphic, relative to the resolution of the screen
        xend - Horizontal position of the bottom-right of the graphic, relative to the resolution of the screen
        yend - Vertical position of the bottom-right of the graphic, relative to the resolution of the screen
        duration - Length of time that the graphic is displayed on the screen
        solid - True if the shape is a solid fill colour, false if it is a stroke outline
        graphiccolor - Fill colour of the graphic object
        shadingcolor - Cyclic shading colour of the graphic object
